WEBVTT

00:09.500 --> 00:11.417
Computer, dispatches.

00:11.458 --> 00:13.000
A research inquiry

00:13.041 --> 00:15.458
from the Manitoba Journal

00:13.041 --> 00:15.458
of Interplanetary Psychology

00:15.500 --> 00:18.291
and three communiques

00:15.500 --> 00:18.291
from your mother.

00:21.917 --> 00:24.834
Transfer the letters from

00:21.917 --> 00:24.834
my mother to the view screen.

00:28.917 --> 00:34.834
And computer, I would like

00:28.917 --> 00:34.834
a real chocolate sundae.

00:34.875 --> 00:38.125
Define "real" in context,

00:34.875 --> 00:38.125
please.

00:38.166 --> 00:39.500
Real.

00:39.542 --> 00:42.709
Not one of your

00:39.542 --> 00:42.709
perfectly synthesized

00:42.750 --> 00:46.041
ingeniously enhanced

00:42.750 --> 00:46.041
imitations.

00:47.959 --> 00:52.208
I would like

00:47.959 --> 00:52.208
real chocolate ice cream,

00:52.250 --> 00:54.458
real whipped cream...

00:54.500 --> 00:55.959
This unit is programmed

00:56.000 --> 00:58.959
to provide sources

00:56.000 --> 00:58.959
of acceptable nutritional value.

00:59.000 --> 01:02.208
Your request does not fall

00:59.000 --> 01:02.208
within current guidelines.

01:02.250 --> 01:03.709
Please indicate whether

01:02.250 --> 01:03.709
you wish

01:03.750 --> 01:05.834
to override

01:03.750 --> 01:05.834
the specified program.

01:05.875 --> 01:07.041
Listen--

01:07.083 --> 01:09.750
PICARD:

01:07.083 --> 01:09.750
Picard to Counselor Troi.

01:09.792 --> 01:12.375
Now what?

01:12.417 --> 01:14.166
Yes, Captain?

01:14.208 --> 01:15.875
The pleasure of your company

01:14.208 --> 01:15.875
is requested, Counselor.

01:15.917 --> 01:18.417
We are, um... we're having

01:15.917 --> 01:18.417
an little impromptu reception

01:18.458 --> 01:20.417
for the arriving delegates.

01:20.458 --> 01:22.583
Captain, I'm not really

01:20.458 --> 01:22.583
dressed for a reception.

01:22.625 --> 01:24.959
Oh, Counselor,

01:22.625 --> 01:24.959
just throw on any old thing.

01:25.000 --> 01:27.250
We're about to get

01:25.000 --> 01:27.250
our first look at the wormhole.

01:27.291 --> 01:28.792
Of course, Captain.

01:28.834 --> 01:30.792
I'm on my way.

01:33.125 --> 01:37.458
God forbid I should miss

01:33.125 --> 01:37.458
my first look at the wormhole.

01:41.750 --> 01:43.375
May I escort you,

01:41.750 --> 01:43.375
Miss Troi?

01:43.417 --> 01:44.959
Just tell me there's

01:43.417 --> 01:44.959
some chocolate here.

01:45.041 --> 01:46.500
PICARD:

01:45.041 --> 01:46.500
Ah, Counselor Troi.

01:46.542 --> 01:49.500
Will you allow me to do

01:46.542 --> 01:49.500
the introductions?

01:49.542 --> 01:51.291
This is Premier Bhavani

01:49.542 --> 01:51.291
of Barzan.

01:51.333 --> 01:52.875
Counselor Deanna Troi.

01:52.917 --> 01:54.291
Your discovery has produced

01:54.333 --> 01:56.709
a great deal of excitement,

01:54.333 --> 01:56.709
Premier.

01:56.750 --> 01:58.083
Hopefully it will

01:56.750 --> 01:58.083
also produce

01:58.125 --> 02:01.041
a new era of prosperity

01:58.125 --> 02:01.041
for my people.

02:01.083 --> 02:02.875
We'll see to that.

02:02.917 --> 02:05.667
You know Mr. Mendoza,

02:02.917 --> 02:05.667
the Federation negotiator.

02:05.709 --> 02:08.625
A pleasure to see you again,

02:05.709 --> 02:08.625
Counselor Troi.

02:08.667 --> 02:11.667
This is a worthy Federation

02:08.667 --> 02:11.667
competitor in the bidding,

02:11.709 --> 02:13.792
Leyor of

02:11.709 --> 02:13.792
the Caldonians.

02:13.834 --> 02:15.208
Madam.

02:15.250 --> 02:18.083
MAN:

02:15.250 --> 02:18.083
And I am

02:15.250 --> 02:18.083
Devinoni Ral.

02:21.500 --> 02:24.125
Ship's Counselor,

02:21.500 --> 02:24.125
Deanna Troi.

02:24.166 --> 02:25.625
MENDOZA:

02:24.166 --> 02:25.625
My good friend

02:24.166 --> 02:25.625
Ral is

02:25.667 --> 02:29.000
the best hired gun

02:25.667 --> 02:29.000
in the business.

02:29.041 --> 02:30.542
Hired gun?

02:30.583 --> 02:33.917
My good friend Mendoza means

02:30.583 --> 02:33.917
that I'm a negotiator

02:33.959 --> 02:36.417
who serves

02:33.959 --> 02:36.417
a variety of clients.

02:36.458 --> 02:39.542
On this particular occasion,

02:36.458 --> 02:39.542
I represent the Chrysalians.

02:39.583 --> 02:42.000
BHAVANI: I believe it's almost

02:39.583 --> 02:42.000
time, isn't it, Captain?

02:42.041 --> 02:43.208
Indeed.

02:43.250 --> 02:45.417
It will be visible

02:43.250 --> 02:45.417
directly ahead.

02:51.125 --> 02:52.875
Is it always on time,

02:51.125 --> 02:52.875
Bhavani?

02:52.917 --> 02:54.333
Always.

02:54.375 --> 02:58.417
We see it every

02:54.375 --> 02:58.417
233 minutes.

02:58.458 --> 02:59.834
Our scientists say

02:58.458 --> 02:59.834
it's due

02:59.875 --> 03:03.208
to radiation buildup

02:59.875 --> 03:03.208
in the accretion disk.

03:03.250 --> 03:06.333
The visible burst

03:03.250 --> 03:06.333
is very brief.

03:10.291 --> 03:13.041
There it is, ladies

03:10.291 --> 03:13.041
and gentlemen, the first

03:13.083 --> 03:16.709
and only stable wormhole

03:13.083 --> 03:16.709
known to exist.

03:17.834 --> 03:20.959
It's yours,

03:17.834 --> 03:20.959
for the right price.

03:53.417 --> 03:58.083
<i>Space, the final frontier.</i>

03:58.125 --> 04:02.500
<i>These are the voyages</i>

03:58.125 --> 04:02.500
<i>of the starship Enterprise.</i>

04:02.542 --> 04:03.750
<i>Its continuing mission--</i>

04:03.792 --> 04:07.583
<i>to explore</i>

04:03.792 --> 04:07.583
<i>strange new worlds,</i>

04:07.625 --> 04:12.208
<i>to seek out new life</i>

04:07.625 --> 04:12.208
<i>and new civilizations,</i>

04:12.250 --> 04:16.291
<i>to boldly go</i>

04:12.250 --> 04:16.291
<i>where no one has gone before.</i>

05:14.875 --> 05:17.667
<i>Captain's log,</i>

05:14.875 --> 05:17.667
<i>Stardate 43385.6.</i>

05:17.709 --> 05:20.834
<i>We are orbiting Barzan Two,</i>

05:17.709 --> 05:20.834
<i>which is entertaining bids</i>

05:20.875 --> 05:24.458
<i>for control of what appears</i>

05:20.875 --> 05:24.458
<i>to be a stable wormhole,</i>

05:24.500 --> 05:26.625
<i>which could provide</i>

05:24.500 --> 05:26.625
<i>a permanent shortcut</i>

05:26.667 --> 05:28.917
<i>to the distant</i>

05:26.667 --> 05:28.917
<i>Gamma Quadrant.</i>

05:28.959 --> 05:30.583
As you all know,

05:30.625 --> 05:32.375
the environment

05:30.625 --> 05:32.375
on my planet

05:32.417 --> 05:36.959
is completely inhospitable

05:32.417 --> 05:36.959
to most other life-forms.

05:37.000 --> 05:39.291
So I'd like to express

05:37.000 --> 05:39.291
my appreciation

05:39.333 --> 05:41.125
to you,

05:39.333 --> 05:41.125
Captain Picard,

05:41.166 --> 05:44.083
for hosting

05:41.166 --> 05:44.083
these negotiations.

05:44.125 --> 05:45.959
The Barzan has been

05:44.125 --> 05:45.959
a society

05:46.000 --> 05:48.917
dependent on others

05:46.000 --> 05:48.917
for generations.

05:48.959 --> 05:51.458
We want that to end.

05:51.500 --> 05:55.542
The appearance of this stable

05:51.500 --> 05:55.542
wormhole in our space

05:55.583 --> 05:59.792
provides us with our first

05:55.583 --> 05:59.792
true natural resource.

05:59.834 --> 06:01.834
We have neither

05:59.834 --> 06:01.834
the experience

06:01.875 --> 06:05.458
nor the technology

06:01.875 --> 06:05.458
to exploit it.

06:05.500 --> 06:07.208
But you do.

06:07.250 --> 06:08.458
RIKER:

06:07.250 --> 06:08.458
Excuse me.

06:08.500 --> 06:10.166
There's a delegation

06:08.500 --> 06:10.166
of Ferengi

06:10.208 --> 06:12.375
that wishes

06:10.208 --> 06:12.375
to be beamed aboard, sir.

06:14.458 --> 06:17.000
Were you expecting

06:14.458 --> 06:17.000
the Ferengi, Premier?

06:17.041 --> 06:20.834
No, but I do not wish

06:17.041 --> 06:20.834
to create ill will, Captain.

06:20.875 --> 06:22.166
If they are interested

06:20.875 --> 06:22.166
in bidding,

06:22.208 --> 06:23.542
I have no objection.

06:25.417 --> 06:27.959
Chief O'Brien,

06:25.417 --> 06:27.959
this is Captain Picard.

06:28.000 --> 06:29.625
Will you beam

06:28.000 --> 06:29.625
the Ferengi directly

06:29.667 --> 06:30.917
to the observation lounge?

06:30.959 --> 06:32.333
O'BRIEN:

06:30.959 --> 06:32.333
Aye, sir.

06:38.291 --> 06:40.959
On behalf of all Ferengi,

06:38.291 --> 06:40.959
I protest.

06:41.000 --> 06:42.834
Why were we not invited

06:41.000 --> 06:42.834
to these negotiations?

06:42.875 --> 06:44.417
BHAVANI:

06:42.875 --> 06:44.417
My apologies.

06:44.458 --> 06:46.542
We did not anticipate

06:44.458 --> 06:46.542
your interest.

06:46.583 --> 06:48.667
You're welcome

06:46.583 --> 06:48.667
to join us.

06:48.709 --> 06:50.333
My name is DaiMon Goss.

06:50.375 --> 06:53.709
And these are my consuls,

06:50.375 --> 06:53.709
Kol and Dr. Arridor.

06:53.750 --> 06:55.250
We'll need chairs.

06:55.291 --> 06:56.792
I'm Captain Picard

06:55.291 --> 06:56.792
of the<i> Enterprise.</i>

06:56.834 --> 06:59.208
I am serving as host

06:56.834 --> 06:59.208
for these proceedings.

06:59.250 --> 07:01.458
Good, then see to it

06:59.250 --> 07:01.458
we get some chairs.

07:01.500 --> 07:02.959
Let me explain--

07:03.000 --> 07:04.875
Fine, fine, just have

07:03.000 --> 07:04.875
your Klingon servant

07:04.917 --> 07:06.125
get us some chairs.

07:06.166 --> 07:08.542
I'm in charge

07:06.166 --> 07:08.542
of security.

07:08.583 --> 07:11.625
Then who gets

07:08.583 --> 07:11.625
the chairs?

07:11.667 --> 07:14.542
DaiMon, due to

07:11.667 --> 07:14.542
the delicate nature

07:14.583 --> 07:17.208
of these negotiations,

07:14.583 --> 07:17.208
all parties

07:17.250 --> 07:19.583
have agreed that

07:17.250 --> 07:19.583
one representative

07:19.625 --> 07:21.667
will suffice. Now I will

07:19.625 --> 07:21.667
be happy to provide

07:21.709 --> 07:23.041
your consuls

07:21.709 --> 07:23.041
with accommodations

07:23.083 --> 07:26.875
and<i> you</i> may have

07:23.083 --> 07:26.875
<i>my</i> chair.

07:26.917 --> 07:29.125
Very well.

07:29.166 --> 07:31.083
Premier.

07:35.417 --> 07:38.583
<i>( sighs )</i>

07:38.625 --> 07:40.417
Kol, the bag.

07:40.458 --> 07:42.792
RIKER:

07:40.458 --> 07:42.792
Gentlemen, this way.

07:42.834 --> 07:45.500
We can handle all

07:42.834 --> 07:45.500
the pleasantries later.

07:45.542 --> 07:48.125
Now, let's get

07:45.542 --> 07:48.125
down to business.

07:51.208 --> 07:53.208
I'll match anyone's

07:51.208 --> 07:53.208
best offer

07:53.250 --> 07:57.250
<i>and</i> add the gold

07:53.250 --> 07:57.250
on top of it.

07:58.500 --> 08:00.458
<i>( chuckling )</i>

08:01.792 --> 08:04.792
COMPUTER:

08:01.792 --> 08:04.792
Devinoni Ral,

08:01.792 --> 08:04.792
human, age 41.

08:04.834 --> 08:07.291
Born Brussels,

08:04.834 --> 08:07.291
European Alliance.

08:07.333 --> 08:09.792
Relocated at age 19

08:07.333 --> 08:09.792
to Hurkos Three.

08:09.834 --> 08:11.834
(<i> door chimes</i> )

08:09.834 --> 08:11.834
Come in.

08:18.917 --> 08:21.041
Should I call

08:18.917 --> 08:21.041
for an appointment?

08:21.083 --> 08:23.041
No.

08:23.083 --> 08:25.583
I was just looking

08:23.083 --> 08:25.583
over some personnel files.

08:25.625 --> 08:27.583
Well, that's too bad.

08:27.625 --> 08:30.375
Thought you might

08:27.625 --> 08:30.375
be thinking about me.

08:30.417 --> 08:33.583
I thought you'd be deep

08:30.417 --> 08:33.583
in negotiations by now.

08:33.625 --> 08:35.208
In recess.

08:37.041 --> 08:39.333
I never play the opening

08:37.041 --> 08:39.333
rounds, anyway.

08:39.375 --> 08:42.250
Inconsequential.

08:42.291 --> 08:43.458
Besides, there are

08:42.291 --> 08:43.458
much better things

08:43.500 --> 08:46.709
to negotiate

08:43.500 --> 08:46.709
on this ship...

08:46.750 --> 08:49.000
like dinner tonight?

08:49.041 --> 08:51.750
What about your

08:49.041 --> 08:51.750
traveling companion?

08:52.959 --> 08:56.917
My traveling companion

08:52.959 --> 08:56.917
is... traveling.

08:58.125 --> 09:00.667
I sent her home.

09:00.709 --> 09:02.917
Why?

09:02.959 --> 09:04.959
You know why.

09:05.959 --> 09:09.125
Weren't you

09:05.959 --> 09:09.125
getting along?

09:09.166 --> 09:11.542
Don't do that.

09:09.166 --> 09:11.542
What?

09:11.583 --> 09:15.333
Don't do

09:11.583 --> 09:15.333
"Counselor" Troi.

09:15.375 --> 09:18.041
Was I?

09:15.375 --> 09:18.041
Yes, you were.

09:24.417 --> 09:27.291
When you leave

09:24.417 --> 09:27.291
this office...

09:27.333 --> 09:29.291
who are you?

09:30.458 --> 09:33.834
Oh, so that's

09:30.458 --> 09:33.834
how it goes.

09:33.875 --> 09:37.375
You never do.

09:37.417 --> 09:39.083
You never do...

09:39.125 --> 09:43.458
leave...

09:39.125 --> 09:43.458
the office.

09:43.500 --> 09:46.125
What are--

09:43.500 --> 09:46.125
Shh-shh-shh.

10:00.959 --> 10:02.959
Dinner at 8:00?

10:20.709 --> 10:23.166
The readings from the Barzans'

10:20.709 --> 10:23.166
probe of the wormhole

10:23.208 --> 10:25.083
are quite impressive,

10:23.208 --> 10:25.083
Captain.

10:25.125 --> 10:27.291
The wormhole

10:25.125 --> 10:27.291
delivered the probe

10:27.333 --> 10:30.208
beyond the Denkiri Arm

10:27.333 --> 10:30.208
in the Gamma Quadrant.

10:30.250 --> 10:32.125
(<i> whistles</i> )

10:33.458 --> 10:35.250
It would take nearly

10:33.458 --> 10:35.250
a century at warp 9

10:35.291 --> 10:36.959
to cover

10:35.291 --> 10:36.959
that distance.

10:37.000 --> 10:39.166
The same distance could be

10:37.000 --> 10:39.166
achieved in a matter of seconds

10:39.208 --> 10:41.291
through the wormhole.

10:39.208 --> 10:41.291
Mm.

10:41.333 --> 10:44.500
Imagine the Ferengi, collecting

10:41.333 --> 10:44.500
tolls if we lose to them.

10:44.542 --> 10:46.125
I don't think

10:44.542 --> 10:46.125
the Ferengi are

10:46.166 --> 10:48.417
the greatest threat

10:46.166 --> 10:48.417
at the table.

10:48.458 --> 10:50.959
With all of

10:48.458 --> 10:50.959
DaiMon Goss's bluster,

10:51.000 --> 10:53.000
they don't have the resources

10:51.000 --> 10:53.000
the Barzans need.

10:53.041 --> 10:55.709
Mm-hmm. I think

10:53.041 --> 10:55.709
that Devinoni

10:55.750 --> 10:58.917
is the one that we need

10:55.750 --> 10:58.917
to watch out for.

10:58.959 --> 11:00.750
An accurate observation.

11:00.792 --> 11:02.375
How did you

11:00.792 --> 11:02.375
recognize that?

11:02.417 --> 11:04.417
Well he was the most

11:02.417 --> 11:04.417
comfortable one in the group.

11:04.458 --> 11:06.375
You must play poker,

11:04.458 --> 11:06.375
Commander.

11:06.417 --> 11:10.208
Poker? Is that a game

11:06.417 --> 11:10.208
of some sort?

11:10.250 --> 11:13.291
Commander Riker conducts

11:10.250 --> 11:13.291
master classes in poker.

11:14.542 --> 11:16.875
Our skills are

11:14.542 --> 11:16.875
not dissimilar, Commander.

11:16.917 --> 11:20.291
Mr. Mendoza, if this

11:16.917 --> 11:20.291
lives up to its billing,

11:20.333 --> 11:24.542
it will be a discovery

11:20.333 --> 11:24.542
of extraordinary value.

11:24.583 --> 11:26.750
But it is

11:24.583 --> 11:26.750
a very big "if."

11:26.792 --> 11:28.917
a wormhole is there one moment

11:26.792 --> 11:28.917
and then gone the next.

11:28.959 --> 11:31.041
A stable wormhole

11:28.959 --> 11:31.041
is unheard of.

11:31.083 --> 11:33.667
Are you saying this

11:31.083 --> 11:33.667
may not be what it seems?

11:33.709 --> 11:35.709
The Barzans do not have

11:33.709 --> 11:35.709
manned space travel,

11:35.750 --> 11:38.208
so they had to resort to

11:35.750 --> 11:38.208
an automated probe.

11:38.250 --> 11:39.792
Its findings are limited.

11:39.834 --> 11:41.792
It cannot be determined

11:39.834 --> 11:41.792
from these charts

11:41.834 --> 11:44.208
how stable

11:41.834 --> 11:44.208
the wormhole<i> really</i> is,

11:44.250 --> 11:46.250
or how long it will

11:44.250 --> 11:46.250
remain intact.

11:46.291 --> 11:47.834
The Federation

11:46.291 --> 11:47.834
could end up buying

11:47.875 --> 11:50.208
a proverbial lemon.

11:50.250 --> 11:51.750
"Proverbial lemon"?

11:51.792 --> 11:53.417
Later, data.

11:51.792 --> 11:53.417
Aye, sir.

11:53.458 --> 11:54.917
And of course,

11:53.458 --> 11:54.917
that means

11:54.959 --> 11:56.917
once the contract

11:54.959 --> 11:56.917
is negotiated and closed,

11:56.959 --> 11:59.583
we would be obliged

11:56.959 --> 11:59.583
to fulfill the terms.

11:59.625 --> 12:01.792
I think we should take a look

11:59.625 --> 12:01.792
for ourselves.

12:01.834 --> 12:03.709
I don't think Bhavani

12:01.834 --> 12:03.709
could object to that.

12:03.750 --> 12:05.792
Geordi has been in

12:03.750 --> 12:05.792
continuous visual contact

12:05.834 --> 12:07.041
with the wormhole,

12:05.834 --> 12:07.041
Captain.

12:07.083 --> 12:08.291
I think it's

12:07.083 --> 12:08.291
a logical choice.

12:08.333 --> 12:09.792
I would also like

12:08.333 --> 12:09.792
to volunteer, sir.

12:09.834 --> 12:11.417
Mm, nobody's going in there

12:09.834 --> 12:11.417
until we have done

12:11.458 --> 12:14.375
a full sensor

12:11.458 --> 12:14.375
analysis.

12:14.417 --> 12:15.875
I want to do everything possible

12:14.417 --> 12:15.875
to determine

12:15.917 --> 12:18.709
that it is safe,

12:15.917 --> 12:18.709
and when I am satisfied

12:18.750 --> 12:20.875
then you, Data,

12:18.750 --> 12:20.875
and Commander La Forge

12:20.917 --> 12:24.750
will enter the wormhole,

12:20.917 --> 12:24.750
tomorrow.

12:26.208 --> 12:30.625
Just a moment of discomfort

12:26.208 --> 12:30.625
for a good cause, DaiMon.

12:30.667 --> 12:34.125
You understand this

12:30.667 --> 12:34.125
will not be lethal?

12:34.166 --> 12:35.709
Doctor,

12:34.166 --> 12:35.709
you surprise me.

12:35.750 --> 12:37.834
I have no wish

12:35.750 --> 12:37.834
to kill anyone.

12:37.875 --> 12:40.458
A short-term crippling

