27:12.000 --> 27:13.792
well...

27:13.834 --> 27:16.625
Go on, please.

27:16.667 --> 27:21.417
Well, scholars don't always

27:16.667 --> 27:21.417
enjoy administrative demands.

27:21.458 --> 27:22.875
And certainly

27:21.458 --> 27:22.875
we've seen here

27:22.917 --> 27:24.125
that the administration

27:24.166 --> 27:27.917
of the wormhole is--

27:24.166 --> 27:27.917
Yes, I must admit,

27:27.959 --> 27:31.417
I have begun to feel

27:27.959 --> 27:31.417
some trepidation about that.

27:33.083 --> 27:34.959
Yes.

27:35.000 --> 27:38.417
Yes, I'm sure

27:35.000 --> 27:38.417
you have, Leyor.

27:38.458 --> 27:40.500
I'm sure we all have.

27:40.542 --> 27:43.250
Do you realize that

27:40.542 --> 27:43.250
in the next century,

27:43.291 --> 27:44.917
the number of ships

27:43.291 --> 27:44.917
that will pass...

27:44.959 --> 27:47.333
Gentlemen, this open session

27:44.959 --> 27:47.333
is called by request

27:47.375 --> 27:49.667
of the Caldonia

27:47.375 --> 27:49.667
delegation.

27:51.709 --> 27:53.041
Madame Bhavani,

27:53.083 --> 27:56.417
Caldonia withdraws

27:53.083 --> 27:56.417
from these proceedings.

27:56.458 --> 27:58.583
For what reasons,

27:56.458 --> 27:58.583
Leyor?

27:58.625 --> 28:00.917
It has been made very clear

27:58.625 --> 28:00.917
that the maintenance

28:00.959 --> 28:02.291
and administrative requirements

28:02.333 --> 28:04.709
are beyond our abilities.

28:04.750 --> 28:06.583
Leyor, the Federation

28:04.750 --> 28:06.583
would like

28:06.625 --> 28:08.250
to negotiate

28:06.625 --> 28:08.250
a trade agreement

28:08.291 --> 28:10.875
in which we could acquire

28:08.291 --> 28:10.875
your planet's rich deposits

28:10.917 --> 28:14.166
of Trillium 323,

28:10.917 --> 28:14.166
which we would add to our bid,

28:14.208 --> 28:15.709
Premier Bhavani.

28:15.750 --> 28:17.125
My apologies.

28:17.166 --> 28:18.709
We have already reached

28:17.166 --> 28:18.709
an agreement

28:18.750 --> 28:20.083
with the Chrysalians.

28:26.458 --> 28:28.166
Mr. Ral...

28:28.208 --> 28:30.166
you either had

28:28.208 --> 28:30.166
very good instincts

28:30.208 --> 28:33.917
or a foreknowledge

28:30.208 --> 28:33.917
of the Caldonian withdrawal.

28:33.959 --> 28:36.166
Well, some people just don't

28:33.959 --> 28:36.166
like to transact business

28:36.208 --> 28:38.583
with the Federation,

28:36.208 --> 28:38.583
Commander.

28:38.625 --> 28:40.625
The Chrysalians

28:38.625 --> 28:40.625
hereby add

28:40.667 --> 28:45.667
the Caldonian Trillium 323

28:40.667 --> 28:45.667
to its bid, Premier.

28:55.000 --> 28:56.917
I'm telling you,

28:55.000 --> 28:56.917
it's changing.

28:56.959 --> 28:58.625
I can see it

28:56.959 --> 28:58.625
with my visor.

28:58.667 --> 29:00.792
I have no intention

28:58.667 --> 29:00.792
of leaving yet.

29:00.834 --> 29:02.792
We have not finished taking

29:00.834 --> 29:02.792
our readings.

29:02.834 --> 29:03.959
Listen, Doctor,

29:04.000 --> 29:05.208
your readings must

29:04.000 --> 29:05.208
be telling you

29:05.250 --> 29:06.500
the same things

29:05.250 --> 29:06.500
we're getting.

29:06.542 --> 29:08.667
This is not

29:06.542 --> 29:08.667
the Gamma Quadrant.

29:08.709 --> 29:11.500
I will not confirm

29:08.709 --> 29:11.500
your speculations.

29:11.542 --> 29:13.709
This is not

29:11.542 --> 29:13.709
a speculation, Doctor.

29:13.750 --> 29:15.875
We are not where the Barzans

29:13.750 --> 29:15.875
said we should be,

29:15.917 --> 29:19.041
which would indicate this side

29:15.917 --> 29:19.041
of the wormhole is not stable.

29:19.083 --> 29:21.917
There are meson

29:19.083 --> 29:21.917
and lepton fluctuations.

29:21.959 --> 29:24.583
Local gravitational fields

29:21.959 --> 29:24.583
are increasing exponentially.

29:24.625 --> 29:26.709
Everything says we better get

29:24.625 --> 29:26.709
the hell out of here.

29:26.750 --> 29:29.583
It will be visible again

29:26.750 --> 29:29.583
in 40 seconds.

29:29.625 --> 29:31.458
We will make

29:29.625 --> 29:31.458
our own judgments then.

29:31.500 --> 29:33.125
I can see it now

29:31.500 --> 29:33.125
and I'm telling you,

29:33.166 --> 29:36.250
you don't have time to wait,

29:33.166 --> 29:36.250
not even 40 seconds.

29:36.291 --> 29:37.750
Ferengi pod, out.

29:37.792 --> 29:39.250
Damn it, Arridor!

29:39.291 --> 29:41.041
We're 70,000

29:39.291 --> 29:41.041
light years

29:41.083 --> 29:43.000
away from our ships.

29:41.083 --> 29:43.000
Come on now!

29:43.041 --> 29:45.750
Follow us in.

29:43.041 --> 29:45.750
We'll lead you.

29:49.000 --> 29:51.000
Idiots.

29:53.000 --> 29:55.375
It's getting worse.

29:55.417 --> 29:58.917
I'm taking us in, Data,

29:55.417 --> 29:58.917
with or without them.

29:58.959 --> 30:00.709
Thrusters at half power...

30:00.750 --> 30:01.959
three-quarters...

30:02.000 --> 30:04.750
Entering outer

30:02.000 --> 30:04.750
event horizon.

30:10.583 --> 30:13.667
They panic quickly

30:10.583 --> 30:13.667
under pressure.

30:15.792 --> 30:17.000
There...

30:17.041 --> 30:18.458
precisely as scheduled,

30:18.500 --> 30:20.875
right where

30:18.500 --> 30:20.875
I expected it to be.

30:31.875 --> 30:33.291
Everyone was talking today

30:33.333 --> 30:37.333
about the way you absorbed

30:33.333 --> 30:37.333
the Caldonian bid.

30:37.375 --> 30:38.917
Well, the opening

30:37.375 --> 30:38.917
was there.

30:38.959 --> 30:40.625
I took it.

30:40.667 --> 30:43.333
Commander Riker didn't know

30:40.667 --> 30:43.333
how you managed it.

30:44.750 --> 30:47.792
Let me tell you something

30:44.750 --> 30:47.792
about Commander Riker.

30:47.834 --> 30:49.291
He's good.

30:49.333 --> 30:51.792
He's the most dangerous man

30:49.333 --> 30:51.792
in that room to me.

30:51.834 --> 30:55.375
But, he doesn't have

30:51.834 --> 30:55.375
an edge...

30:55.417 --> 30:56.667
your edge.

30:56.709 --> 30:59.834
<i>Our</i> edge.

30:59.875 --> 31:02.750
You make it sound

30:59.875 --> 31:02.750
unethical.

31:02.792 --> 31:05.250
Isn't it?

31:05.291 --> 31:08.792
Deanna...

31:05.291 --> 31:08.792
it's just business.

31:14.083 --> 31:16.875
Why haven't you told anyone

31:14.083 --> 31:16.875
you're an empath?

31:18.250 --> 31:20.709
Because I find it makes

31:18.250 --> 31:20.709
people uncomfortable.

31:22.667 --> 31:26.500
I think you don't tell them

31:22.667 --> 31:26.500
so you can gain an advantage.

31:28.125 --> 31:31.625
Well I gained an advantage

31:28.125 --> 31:31.625
by using it with you.

31:31.667 --> 31:33.834
You didn't seem

31:31.667 --> 31:33.834
to mind that.

31:39.375 --> 31:42.583
Look, Deanna...

31:42.625 --> 31:46.333
the point of negotiating

31:42.625 --> 31:46.333
is to take advantage.

31:46.375 --> 31:48.250
I don't know what the other side

31:46.375 --> 31:48.250
is offering,

31:48.291 --> 31:50.542
and they don't know

31:48.291 --> 31:50.542
what I'm offering.

31:50.583 --> 31:53.750
So we dance around each other

31:50.583 --> 31:53.750
until somebody wins.

31:53.792 --> 31:56.959
I never cry foul

31:53.792 --> 31:56.959
when I lose.

31:57.000 --> 32:00.041
But you're reading

31:57.000 --> 32:00.041
their emotional states,

32:00.083 --> 32:01.417
their inner selves,

32:01.458 --> 32:03.542
and then using that

32:01.458 --> 32:03.542
to manipulate them.

32:03.583 --> 32:06.667
Well people have done that

32:03.583 --> 32:06.667
for thousands of years,

32:06.709 --> 32:08.792
just by listening

32:06.709 --> 32:08.792
carefully,

32:08.834 --> 32:11.000
by watching

32:08.834 --> 32:11.000
body language.

32:11.041 --> 32:13.333
I just happen

32:11.041 --> 32:13.333
to be better at it.

32:13.375 --> 32:15.166
You do it.

32:15.208 --> 32:18.959
I do it to help my crew,

32:15.208 --> 32:18.959
not outmaneuver them.

32:20.291 --> 32:22.417
And I don't hide

32:20.291 --> 32:22.417
that I'm an empath.

32:22.458 --> 32:23.750
Oh, so you

32:22.458 --> 32:23.750
announce it

32:23.792 --> 32:27.083
to every alien culture

32:23.792 --> 32:27.083
you encounter?

32:27.125 --> 32:31.500
Or do you use it to give

32:27.125 --> 32:31.500
your side an advantage?

32:31.542 --> 32:33.542
Do you tell the Romulan

32:31.542 --> 32:33.542
that's about to attack

32:33.583 --> 32:36.166
that you sense that

32:33.583 --> 32:36.166
he may be bluffing?

32:36.208 --> 32:38.250
Or do you just tell it

32:36.208 --> 32:38.250
to your captain?

32:44.083 --> 32:46.417
That's different.

32:46.458 --> 32:48.417
That's a matter

32:46.458 --> 32:48.417
of protection.

32:48.458 --> 32:51.875
Yes, protection.

32:48.458 --> 32:51.875
Your protection,

32:51.917 --> 32:57.250
your captain,

32:51.917 --> 32:57.250
your crew, your edge.

32:57.291 --> 32:59.250
Yes.

33:00.500 --> 33:01.709
Now, it's a matter

33:00.500 --> 33:01.709
of life and death

33:01.750 --> 33:03.000
when you take

33:01.750 --> 33:03.000
the advantage.

33:03.041 --> 33:08.375
Me, I deal in property,

33:03.041 --> 33:08.375
exchanges.

33:08.417 --> 33:11.208
Nobody gets hurt.

33:11.250 --> 33:13.166
So you tell me...

33:13.208 --> 33:14.458
which one of us

33:13.208 --> 33:14.458
would you say

33:14.500 --> 33:17.333
has more of a problem

33:14.500 --> 33:17.333
with ethics?

33:19.583 --> 33:21.041
Excuse me.

33:48.667 --> 33:50.834
May I join you,

33:48.667 --> 33:50.834
Commander?

33:53.291 --> 33:55.250
Bought out

33:53.291 --> 33:55.250
the Ferengi yet, Ral?

33:55.291 --> 33:56.792
Think I should

33:55.291 --> 33:56.792
give it a try?

33:56.834 --> 33:58.583
No, but I think that you will.

33:56.834 --> 33:58.583
One way or another,

33:58.625 --> 34:01.041
it's gonna come down

33:58.625 --> 34:01.041
to you and me.

34:01.083 --> 34:02.583
You know, you're very

34:01.083 --> 34:02.583
good at this.

34:02.625 --> 34:03.750
Very good.

34:03.792 --> 34:05.166
Much better

34:03.792 --> 34:05.166
than you realize.

34:05.208 --> 34:07.333
Well, I hope I'm better

34:05.208 --> 34:07.333
than<i> you</i> realize.

34:07.375 --> 34:08.917
The last mile

34:07.375 --> 34:08.917
of the marathon

34:08.959 --> 34:10.667
is always

34:08.959 --> 34:10.667
the toughest.

34:10.709 --> 34:12.250
That's when the winners

34:10.709 --> 34:12.250
are willing

34:12.291 --> 34:14.250
to take the big risks.

34:15.166 --> 34:16.417
You willing

34:15.166 --> 34:16.417
to do that?

34:16.458 --> 34:17.667
We'll see, won't we?

34:17.709 --> 34:19.083
Well, let's see now.

34:19.125 --> 34:21.583
I'm prepared to reach a firm

34:19.125 --> 34:21.583
agreement with Bhavani

34:21.625 --> 34:24.875
before we learn the outcome

34:21.625 --> 34:24.875
of your probe's expedition.

34:24.917 --> 34:27.417
Are you?

34:27.458 --> 34:29.208
Oh, well, well, well.

34:29.250 --> 34:31.000
That would not be

34:29.250 --> 34:31.000
looked upon favorably

34:31.041 --> 34:33.291
by the Federation,

34:31.041 --> 34:33.291
I'd imagine.

34:33.333 --> 34:34.500
You see, you have to

34:33.333 --> 34:34.500
be willing

34:34.542 --> 34:37.834
to take that

34:34.542 --> 34:37.834
last step<i> alone,</i>

34:37.875 --> 34:39.625
or it just isn't

34:37.875 --> 34:39.625
worth playing.

34:39.667 --> 34:41.041
Your point of view,

34:39.667 --> 34:41.041
not mine.

34:41.083 --> 34:43.583
Oh, I see that,

34:41.083 --> 34:43.583
Commander, I see that.

34:43.625 --> 34:47.166
Otherwise, you wouldn't be

34:43.625 --> 34:47.166
<i>second</i> in command

34:47.208 --> 34:49.417
of this starship.

34:49.458 --> 34:50.875
You know, I feel

34:50.917 --> 34:54.458
responsible for you

34:50.917 --> 34:54.458
in a way... related.

34:56.375 --> 34:59.041
Deanna.

34:59.083 --> 35:01.583
We both love Deanna.

35:01.625 --> 35:03.917
Oh, in different ways,

35:01.625 --> 35:03.917
of course.

35:03.959 --> 35:08.000
I will remove that burden

35:03.959 --> 35:08.000
of responsibility right now.

35:08.041 --> 35:10.583
My relationship with Deanna

35:08.041 --> 35:10.583
stands very well on its own

35:10.625 --> 35:11.834
without any help

35:10.625 --> 35:11.834
from you.

35:11.875 --> 35:13.417
Of course it does,

35:11.875 --> 35:13.417
of course it does.

35:13.458 --> 35:17.000
It's just that,

35:13.458 --> 35:17.000
well...

35:17.041 --> 35:19.583
she's a remarkable woman.

35:19.625 --> 35:22.542
Brilliant, lovely...

35:24.333 --> 35:26.458
very passionate.

35:26.500 --> 35:28.709
And she could have

35:26.500 --> 35:28.709
been yours, Will.

35:28.750 --> 35:32.375
But you just didn't do enough

35:28.750 --> 35:32.375
to keep her.

35:32.417 --> 35:35.375
And now, well...

35:35.417 --> 35:38.083
I'm here.

35:38.125 --> 35:40.208
And I'm going

35:38.125 --> 35:40.208
to take her, too.

35:44.417 --> 35:47.125
That's the first bad play

35:44.417 --> 35:47.125
I've seen you make.

35:47.166 --> 35:50.125
If you can bring happiness

35:47.166 --> 35:50.125
into Deanna's life,

35:50.166 --> 35:53.083
nothing would

35:50.166 --> 35:53.083
please me more.

35:53.125 --> 35:55.875
You know you're not really

35:53.125 --> 35:55.875
such a bad sort, Ral,

35:55.917 --> 35:57.625
except you don't have

35:55.917 --> 35:57.625
any values

35:57.667 --> 36:00.750
beyond the value

35:57.667 --> 36:00.750
of today's bid, that is.

36:02.166 --> 36:06.166
Deanna is just the woman

36:02.166 --> 36:06.166
to bring some meaning

36:06.208 --> 36:07.667
to your sorry existence,

36:07.709 --> 36:10.417
if you're smart enough

36:07.709 --> 36:10.417
to take it.

36:10.458 --> 36:12.500
I doubt that you are.

36:14.500 --> 36:16.500
To the last mile.

36:29.250 --> 36:31.917
Sir, the Ferengi vessel

36:29.250 --> 36:31.917
is moving

36:31.959 --> 36:35.041
out of orbit--

36:31.959 --> 36:35.041
impulse power.

36:35.083 --> 36:39.000
They are approaching the entry

36:35.083 --> 36:39.000
to the wormhole, sir.

36:39.041 --> 36:42.250
Computer, is the Ferengi Goss

36:39.041 --> 36:42.250
still on board the<i> Enterprise?</i>

36:42.291 --> 36:45.333
DaiMon Goss departed

36:42.291 --> 36:45.333
the<i> Enterprise</i> at 1400 hours.

36:45.375 --> 36:47.166
They are powering forward

36:45.375 --> 36:47.166
missile launchers, sir.

36:47.208 --> 36:49.834
Yellow alert.

36:47.208 --> 36:49.834
Hail the Ferengi.

36:52.041 --> 36:54.667
Request an explanation of

36:52.041 --> 36:54.667
your actions, DaiMon Goss.

36:54.709 --> 36:56.834
I have learned

36:54.709 --> 36:56.834
from informed sources

36:56.875 --> 36:58.542
that the Federation

36:56.875 --> 36:58.542
has manipulated

36:58.583 --> 37:01.375
these negotiations from

36:58.583 --> 37:01.375
the very beginning,

37:01.417 --> 37:04.208
and has already signed a secret

37:01.417 --> 37:04.208
agreement with the Barzans.

37:04.250 --> 37:05.667
That is not true.

37:05.709 --> 37:09.083
The Ferengi offer was

37:05.709 --> 37:09.083
never seriously considered.

37:09.125 --> 37:12.166
Premier Bhavani welcomed you

37:09.125 --> 37:12.166
to these proceedings

37:12.208 --> 37:14.041
despite my better judgment.

37:14.083 --> 37:16.625
We will be ignored

37:14.083 --> 37:16.625
no longer.

37:18.166 --> 37:20.250
They've fired a missile

37:18.166 --> 37:20.250
directly at the opening, sir.

37:20.291 --> 37:22.333
Destroy it.

37:20.291 --> 37:22.333
On screen.

37:22.375 --> 37:24.417
Firing phasers.

37:28.709 --> 37:32.500
Your offers both

37:28.709 --> 37:32.500
have merit, gentlemen.

37:32.542 --> 37:33.792
If I could find

37:32.542 --> 37:33.792
a deciding factor--

37:33.834 --> 37:36.291
(<i> alarm klaxon blaring</i> )

37:36.333 --> 37:38.458
Riker to Picard.

37:36.333 --> 37:38.458
What's happening, Captain?

37:38.500 --> 37:40.917
Goss has fired a missile

37:38.500 --> 37:40.917
at the wormhole.

37:40.959 --> 37:42.458
I need you on the bridge,

37:40.959 --> 37:42.458
Number One.

37:42.500 --> 37:44.458
Excuse me.

37:47.750 --> 37:50.917
Excuse me for saying so under

37:47.750 --> 37:50.917
the circumstances, Premier,

37:50.959 --> 37:53.375
but this fight

37:50.959 --> 37:53.375
seems to really be

37:53.417 --> 37:56.750
between the Federation

37:53.417 --> 37:56.750
and the Ferengi.

37:56.792 --> 37:59.709
Now, it seems unconscionable

37:56.792 --> 37:59.709
that your wormhole

37:59.750 --> 38:02.709
is being used as a pawn

37:59.750 --> 38:02.709
in their power struggle.

38:04.125 --> 38:06.542
You must know we will not

38:04.125 --> 38:06.542
allow you to do this.

38:06.583 --> 38:09.625
If the Ferengi cannot have

38:06.583 --> 38:09.625
the wormhole, no one will.

38:09.667 --> 38:11.542
A missile will have

38:09.667 --> 38:11.542
no destructive effect

38:11.583 --> 38:12.917
on a wormhole.

38:12.959 --> 38:14.792
But if it should explode

38:12.959 --> 38:14.792
near the shuttlecraft,

38:14.834 --> 38:16.500
they will be destroyed.

38:16.542 --> 38:18.750
Casualties of war,

38:16.542 --> 38:18.750
Captain.

38:18.792 --> 38:22.208
My men are prepared to die.

38:18.792 --> 38:22.208
Are yours?

38:23.125 --> 38:25.500
Captain, he's lying.

38:25.542 --> 38:28.583
I'm almost sure of it.

38:25.542 --> 38:28.583
He doesn't mean what he says.

38:28.625 --> 38:31.000
Why? What is he

38:28.625 --> 38:31.000
doing it for, then?

38:31.041 --> 38:32.750
(<i> door whooshes open</i> )

38:34.917 --> 38:36.625
Permission to enter

38:34.917 --> 38:36.625
the bridge, Captain.

38:36.667 --> 38:38.041
Premier, with all

38:36.667 --> 38:38.041
due respect--

38:38.083 --> 38:40.250
Captain, I believe I am

38:38.083 --> 38:40.250
in a better position

38:40.291 --> 38:42.959
to settle this with DaiMon Goss

38:40.291 --> 38:42.959
than you are.

38:43.000 --> 38:44.792
May I address him?

38:47.041 --> 38:48.625
Premier?

38:57.125 --> 38:58.291
DaiMon Goss?

38:58.333 --> 38:59.542
This is Devinoni Ral.

38:59.583 --> 39:01.709
I have nothing

38:59.583 --> 39:01.709
to say to you, Ral.

39:01.750 --> 39:04.208
Well,

39:01.750 --> 39:04.208
then just listen.

39:04.250 --> 39:06.667
The planet Barzan

39:04.250 --> 39:06.667
has reached an agreement

39:06.709 --> 39:08.458
with the Chrysalians

39:08.500 --> 39:11.041
for long-term control

39:08.500 --> 39:11.041
of the wormhole.

39:11.083 --> 39:13.000
Now, on behalf

39:11.083 --> 39:13.000
of the Chrysalians,

39:13.041 --> 39:14.625
I am prepared to offer

39:13.041 --> 39:14.625
the Ferengi

39:14.667 --> 39:18.375
free access to the wormhole in

39:14.667 --> 39:18.375
perpetuity.

39:18.417 --> 39:19.917
I have your word

39:18.417 --> 39:19.917
on this?

39:19.959 --> 39:22.375
Yes, my word, sir.

39:22.417 --> 39:24.625
In exchange for Ferengi

39:22.417 --> 39:24.625
convoy privileges

39:24.667 --> 39:27.375
to be negotiated

39:24.667 --> 39:27.375
in good faith.

39:27.417 --> 39:29.709
This is an acceptable offer.

39:31.375 --> 39:34.709
The Ferengi vessel has shut down

39:31.375 --> 39:34.709
its forward missile launcher.

39:34.750 --> 39:36.875
Stand down red alert.

39:36.917 --> 39:39.458
Commander Riker...

39:39.500 --> 39:41.083
I'm sorry you

39:39.500 --> 39:41.083
had to learn about

39:41.125 --> 39:43.417
my decision this way.

39:43.458 --> 39:45.959
You represented

39:43.458 --> 39:45.959
the Federation well.

39:46.000 --> 39:47.500
But I have come

39:46.000 --> 39:47.500
to believe

39:47.542 --> 39:49.917
that the Chrysalian's

39:47.542 --> 39:49.917
tradition of peace

39:49.959 --> 39:52.542
is more desirable

39:49.959 --> 39:52.542
to my planet.

39:53.458 --> 39:54.625
Excuse me, Premier.

39:54.667 --> 39:57.542
There's something

39:54.667 --> 39:57.542
you should know.

39:59.667 --> 40:02.333
I'm sorry, was there

39:59.667 --> 40:02.333
something you wanted to say?

40:02.375 --> 40:04.291
No, not at all.

40:04.333 --> 40:06.917
I have sensed you suddenly

40:04.333 --> 40:06.917
felt uncomfortable.

40:08.250 --> 40:11.250
Well, after all, it was

40:08.250 --> 40:11.250
a very tense situation.

40:11.291 --> 40:13.125
But that's what's so odd.

40:13.166 --> 40:15.041
It wasn't tense at all.

40:15.083 --> 40:16.792
In fact,

40:15.083 --> 40:16.792
I sensed no tension

40:16.834 --> 40:18.166
from you or Goss.

40:18.208 --> 40:20.375
Wha-- I--

40:18.208 --> 40:20.375
I was tense!

40:20.417 --> 40:21.917
I was ready to blow it up!

40:21.959 --> 40:24.000
Wha-- I strongly protest!

40:24.041 --> 40:25.667
Screen off.

40:25.709 --> 40:26.834
It was as though

40:25.709 --> 40:26.834
you were

40:26.875 --> 40:29.417
performing a scene

40:26.875 --> 40:29.417
for all of us.

40:30.375 --> 40:31.792
Pardon me, Captain, I--

40:31.834 --> 40:34.125
I believe there's a slight

40:31.834 --> 40:34.125
conflict of interest here.

40:34.166 --> 40:36.625
I agree entirely.

40:36.667 --> 40:39.041
Mr. Ral asked me

40:36.667 --> 40:39.041
not to tell anyone

40:39.083 --> 40:41.834
he has empathic

40:39.083 --> 40:41.834
powers,

40:41.875 --> 40:44.542
which he uses to manipulate

40:41.875 --> 40:44.542
his competitors

40:44.583 --> 40:47.125
in a negotiation.

40:44.583 --> 40:47.125
And, yes,

40:47.166 --> 40:49.834
it did put me in

40:47.166 --> 40:49.834
a conflict of interest,

40:49.875 --> 40:52.208
which I hope

40:49.875 --> 40:52.208
I have now resolved.

40:53.667 --> 40:55.166
Premier, I believe Ral

40:55.208 --> 40:57.583
has used your fear

40:55.208 --> 40:57.583
of continuing aggression

40:57.625 --> 41:00.000
between the Federation

40:57.625 --> 41:00.000
and its enemies

41:00.041 --> 41:03.083
to undermine

41:00.041 --> 41:03.083
our position.

41:03.125 --> 41:05.500
I also believe that

41:03.125 --> 41:05.500
this incident

41:05.542 --> 41:09.000
was staged by Ral and Goss

41:05.542 --> 41:09.000
to provide you a reason

41:09.041 --> 41:12.000
to choose in favor

41:09.041 --> 41:12.000
of the Chrysalians.

41:13.250 --> 41:14.542
Captain, it's

41:13.250 --> 41:14.542
the shuttlecraft,

41:14.583 --> 41:16.041
they're coming

41:14.583 --> 41:16.041
back through.

41:19.250 --> 41:21.208
GEORDI:

41:19.250 --> 41:21.208
Shuttle Nine to<i> Enterprise.</i>

41:21.250 --> 41:22.959
On screen.

41:24.959 --> 41:27.875
This is shuttle Nine

41:24.959 --> 41:27.875
reporting in.

41:27.917 --> 41:29.250
Barely.

41:29.291 --> 41:31.250
PICARD:

41:29.291 --> 41:31.250
And the Ferengi pod, Commander?

41:31.291 --> 41:33.500
Trapped on

41:31.291 --> 41:33.500
the other side, sir.

41:33.542 --> 41:36.041
In Delta Quadrant.

41:33.542 --> 41:36.041
We tried to warn them.

41:36.083 --> 41:37.583
They wouldn't follow us.

41:37.625 --> 41:39.125
Elaborate.

41:39.166 --> 41:43.125
Captain, this end of the

41:39.166 --> 41:43.125
wormhole is currently stable,

41:43.166 --> 41:46.667
but the other end apparently

41:43.166 --> 41:46.667
shifts positions periodically.

41:46.709 --> 41:49.333
The Barzan probe had no way

41:46.709 --> 41:49.333
to recognize this.

41:49.375 --> 41:52.875
Eventually, both sides

41:49.375 --> 41:52.875
will be unstable.

41:52.917 --> 41:55.583
GEORDI: It's a dry well,

41:52.917 --> 41:55.583
Captain-- worthless.

41:55.625 --> 41:57.709
Acknowledged, shuttle.

41:57.750 --> 42:00.750
Main shuttle bay,

41:57.750 --> 42:00.750
prepare for final approach.

42:00.792 --> 42:02.125
MAN:

42:00.792 --> 42:02.125
Aye, sir.

42:02.166 --> 42:04.875
WORF: Captain, DaiMon Goss

42:02.166 --> 42:04.875
is demanding

42:04.917 --> 42:07.583
to know where

42:04.917 --> 42:07.583
his men are.

42:07.625 --> 42:09.458
Advise him to set

42:07.625 --> 42:09.458
his coordinates

42:09.500 --> 42:10.792
for the Delta Quadrant.

42:10.834 --> 42:15.333
He may run into them

42:10.834 --> 42:15.333
in 80 years or so.

42:17.166 --> 42:19.750
Mr. Ral...

42:19.792 --> 42:21.542
congratulations on winning

42:19.792 --> 42:21.542
the rights

42:21.583 --> 42:23.625
to the Barzan wormhole.

42:23.667 --> 42:26.500
I take the risks,

42:23.667 --> 42:26.500
Mr. Riker.

42:26.542 --> 42:29.834
And I stand by

42:26.542 --> 42:29.834
my agreements.

42:33.500 --> 42:35.417
Come in.

42:43.834 --> 42:45.041
When do you leave?

42:45.083 --> 42:46.583
Soon.

42:46.625 --> 42:49.000
I've been recalled

42:46.625 --> 42:49.000
by the Chrysalians.

42:49.041 --> 42:51.083
Explanations demanded,

42:49.041 --> 42:51.083
and so forth.

42:51.125 --> 42:52.625
I'm sorry.

42:52.667 --> 42:54.834
Well, I've done well

42:52.667 --> 42:54.834
for them over the years.

42:54.875 --> 42:56.959
They understand the stakes.

42:57.000 --> 42:59.417
It'll be fine.

43:00.709 --> 43:03.083
I had to do it, Troi.

43:03.125 --> 43:05.875
Bhavani was ready to go

43:03.125 --> 43:05.875
with the Federation.

43:05.917 --> 43:08.291
I sensed it.

43:08.333 --> 43:10.667
I'd used up every card

43:08.333 --> 43:10.667
in the deck.

43:10.709 --> 43:12.458
I needed to change

43:10.709 --> 43:12.458
the rules.

43:12.500 --> 43:14.083
You must have known

43:12.500 --> 43:14.083
I couldn't

43:14.125 --> 43:15.875
allow you to do that.

43:17.792 --> 43:19.125
My human physical response

43:19.166 --> 43:23.291
must have been blocking

43:19.166 --> 43:23.291
my Betazoid senses.

43:26.959 --> 43:29.166
I'm very grateful for

43:26.959 --> 43:29.166
what you did, in a way.

43:31.125 --> 43:33.542
It's made me take

43:31.125 --> 43:33.542
a hard look at who I am.

43:36.000 --> 43:37.667
I don't like what I see.

43:39.000 --> 43:42.250
I once asked you

43:39.000 --> 43:42.250
to run away with me.

43:42.291 --> 43:44.333
Now I'm asking again.

43:46.083 --> 43:49.375
I need you.

43:49.417 --> 43:51.458
You could help me change.

43:49.417 --> 43:51.458
You could--

43:51.500 --> 43:53.625
You could be

43:51.500 --> 43:53.625
my conscience.

44:06.792 --> 44:10.333
I already have a job

44:06.792 --> 44:10.333
as Counselor.
